    "body": "### Steps to reproduce the issue\r\ninstallation seemingly works fine:\r\n```console\r\n$ spack install xgboost\r\n```\r\nuntil I check what is under the prefix directory: apparently the folder \".../xgboost/dmlc-core/include\" from the source files was put under prefix/include and \".../xgboost/dmlc-core/libdmlc.a\" was put in prefix/lib as opposed to the target file \"libxgboost.so\"\r\n\r\n### Platform and user environment\r\n\r\n```commandline\r\n$ uname -a\r\nLinux storm 4.15.0-38-generic #41-Ubuntu SMP Wed Oct 10 10:59:38 UTC 2018 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n $ lsb_release -d\r\nDescription:\tLinux Mint 19 Tara (same as Ubuntu bionic (18.04.1))\r\n``` \r\n### Additional information\r\nI will be creating a PR shortly to fix the problem.\r\n",
